body:
https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0489/

Makes extension module initialisation much more like Python module initialisation by splitting it into a creation and execution phase, and providing all metadata (as ModuleSpec object) that is needed for the module to configure itself before the execution of the global module code.

commit.message: implement PEP 489 multi-phase module initialisation in Py3.5+
make module exec function cname module specific to make it easier to select in a debugger/profiler
minimal implementation of module init procedure for embedding case, ignoring module attributes for now (which we don't know anyway, e.g. __file__ ?)
remove redundant C defines around helper code (already applied where helper is used)
disable file/path name overwriting during module setup in post-PEP489 runtimes (where the ModuleSpec provides proper metadata)
silence C compiler warning about unused argument
disable "initial_file_path" test in Py3.5+ since it's superseded by the ModuleSpec metadata during module initialisation
write warning into generated header file for now to explain that calling the module init function is not enough to initialise the module anymore
make embedding code for PEP 489 less hackish by using the official C-API functions

title: implement PEP 489 multi-phase module initialisation in Py3.5+
